#: ../../doc_files/batch_mode/batch_mode_excel.rst:2
msgid "Batch mode processing with an Excel application"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/batch_mode/batch_mode_excel.rst:5
msgid ""
"**Platform compatibility**: The Excel batch mode described in this "
"section is **Windows-only**. It requires **Microsoft Excel** (32-bit or "
"64-bit) and uses Windows-specific VBA APIs. **LibreOffice Calc and other "
"spreadsheet applications are not supported**. The Excel file is provided "
"as an example to demonstrate the possibility of batch processing, not as "
"a required component for using UncertRadio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/batch_mode/batch_mode_excel.rst:13
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/batch_mode/batch_mode_excel.rst:15
msgid ""
"The automated usage of UncertRadio is of practical value when the UR "
"calls are embedded in another program, which also takes control over the "
"sequence of calls to UR with different project files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/batch_mode/batch_mode_excel.rst:19
msgid ""
"**Example use case**: A user-written program for processing data "
"evaluation for a certain measurement procedure, where a master project "
"file is used for evaluating different batch samples. In this scenario, "
"only a part of the input parameters varies from measurement to "
"measurement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc_files/batch_mode/batch_mode_excel.rst:25
msgid ""
"You must provide a program part which modifies the \"variable\" input "
"parameters in a copy of the master project file based on the :ref:`input "
"format of a TXP project file <structure of the project file>`."
msgstr ""

